body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, my name is Joshua Barnes and I'm a customer service agent at ABC Car Dealership. May I ask for your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Elizabeth. Could you please provide me with the phone number associated with your account?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's five five five, six four three, two one eight nine.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you. Also, may I have your email address for verification purposes?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, it's e l i z a b e t h dot b a r n e s at e x a m p l e dot c o m.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you for providing the information. Is there anything else I can assist you with today, Elizabeth?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, I just needed help with some data management issues. I'm feeling a bit sad about it.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I understand, Elizabeth. I'll make sure to escalate this issue for resolution. Thank you for your time and patience.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Have a great day, Elizabeth. Goodbye.
